org.openntf.domino.mock.interfaces

Interface NotesAdministrationProcess

  • All Superinterfaces:
    NotesBase

    public interface NotesAdministrationProcess
extends NotesBase
    Represents the administration process.
    Author:
    Sven Dreher
    Access:
    To create an AdministrationProcess object, call NotesSession.createAdministrationProcess(String) in Session. All AdministrationProcess methods require unrestricted server access.

      • isCertificateAuthorityAvailable

        boolean isCertificateAuthorityAvailable()
                                        throws NotesApiException
        Indicates whether a certificate authority certifier is available.
        Returns:
        Indicates whether a certificate authority certifier is available.
        Throws:
        NotesApiException
        Legal Values:
        • true in either of the following cases:
          • getCertificateAuthorityOrg() is set and a certificate authority certifier is available for the specified organization.
          • getCertificateAuthorityOrg() is not set and any certificate authority certifier is available.
        • false otherwise

      • isUseCertificateAuthority

        boolean isUseCertificateAuthority()
                                  throws NotesApiException
        Indicates whether to use the certificate authority for certification.
        Returns:
        Indicates whether to use the certificate authority for certification.
        Throws:
        NotesApiException
        Legal Values:
        • true to use the certificate authority
        • false (default) to use a certifier ID file
        Usage:
        If you set this property to true, specify getCertificateAuthorityOrg(). You can ensure that the certifier is available with isCertificateAuthorityAvailable(). If you set this property to false, specify getCertifierFile() and getCertifierPassword().

        Returns:

        Throws:
        NotesApiException
        Usage:
        This method enters the following administration request: Add or Modify Group in Domino Directory. If the group exists, the members are added to that group. If the group does not exist, a new multi-purpose group is created containing the members.

      • addInternetCertificateToUser

        java.lang.String addInternetCertificateToUser(java.lang.String user,
                                            java.lang.String keyRingFile,
                                            java.lang.String keyRingPassword)
                                              throws NotesApiException
        Enters a request in the Administration Requests database to add an Internet certificate to a user ID.
        Parameters:
        user - The full hierarchical name (can be abbreviated) of the user.
        keyRingFile - The pathname of the key ring file containing the Internet certificate.
        keyRingPassword - The password of the key ring file.
        Returns:
        The note ID of an entry created in the Administration Requests database.
        Throws:
        NotesApiException
        Usage:
        The administration process is a program that automates routine administrative tasks. For more information, see "Add Internet Certificate to Person Record" in Administration Help. If this method is used with the certifier ID process, it requires an Internet certificate in a key ring file. See "Creating a server key ring file" in Administration Help. If this method is used with the CA process, no server key ring file is needed, the keyringname$ and keyringpassword$ parameters should be called with null text values "", and the NotesAdministrationProcess object's UseCertificateAuthority property must be set to True prior to calling the method.

      • configureMailAgent

        java.lang.String configureMailAgent(java.lang.String userName,
                                  java.lang.String agentName)
                                    throws NotesApiException
        Enters a request in the Administration Requests database to configure an agent in a mail database on a user's home server.
        Parameters:
        userName - The full hierarchical name (can be abbreviated) of the user.
        agentName - The name of the agent.
        Returns:
        The note ID of an entry created in the Administration Requests database.
        Throws:
        NotesApiException
        Usage:
        This method specifies username as the value of "Run on behalf of" under the Security tab in the Agent Properties box. This is useful to allow scheduled agents on a mail database to run under the authority of the mail user. If activatable is true, users with Editor access can enable and disable the agent without resigning it. After the agent is configured, you can use the NotesAgent class to reset activatable and enable.

                                  java.lang.String agentName,
                                  boolean activatable,
                                  boolean enable)
                                    throws NotesApiException
        Enters a request in the Administration Requests database to configure an agent in a mail database on a user's home server.
        Parameters:
        userName - The full hierarchical name (can be abbreviated) of the user.
        agentName - The name of the agent.
        activatable -
        • true (default) to make the agent activatable
        • false to make the agent not activatable
        enable -
        • true (default) to enable the agent
        • false to disable the agent
        Returns:
        The note ID of an entry created in the Administration Requests database.
        Throws:
        NotesApiException
        Usage:
        This method specifies username as the value of "Run on behalf of" under the Security tab in the Agent Properties box. This is useful to allow scheduled agents on a mail database to run under the authority of the mail user. If activatable is true, users with Editor access can enable and disable the agent without resigning it. After the agent is configured, you can use the NotesAgent class to reset activatable and enable.

        • NotesAdministrationProcess.PWD_CHK_DONTCHECKPASSWORD does not require the user to enter a password when authenticating with other servers (default)
        • NotesAdministrationProcess.PWD_CHK_LOCKOUT prevents the user from accessing servers that have password checking enabled
        notesPasswordChangeInterval - Required change interval - number of days at which the user must supply a new password. Defaults to zero.
        notesPasswordGracePeriod - Grace period (in days) for changing the password. Defaults to zero.
        internetPasswordForceChange -
        • true to force the user to change the password on next login
        • false to not force the user to change the password (default)
        Returns:
        The note ID of an entry created in the Administration Requests database.
        Throws:
        NotesApiException
        Usage:
        Specify null to take the default for the optional parameters 2-5. At least one optional parameter must be specified.
